So if you had to live in the middle of America&#039;s fourth-largest city, would you choose to be crammed down in the flats?Â  If you wanted a view, would you have an airless apartment up some filing cabinet?Â  Or live up the side of some godforsaken hill covered in winding roads and devoid of parking?&lt;br /&gt;
